An angry mob has set ablaze a suspected motorcycle thief in Wurukum, Makurdi Benue state capital. The Nation gathered the victim snatched a commercial motorcycle from the owner at the high-level area at gunpoint and was heading towards Wurukum. Luck however ran against him as the owner raised the alarm, which attracted residents who gave him a hot chase. It was gathered they caught up with him close to LGEA primary school Wurukum popularly called Suswam thank you. The mob immediately tied his hands, poured petrol all over his body with firewood and set him ablaze. The Police spoke persons Kate Anene, a DSP, confirmed the incident and warned the public to desist from jungle justice. His corpse was still at the scene of the incident as at the time of filing this report.